"1340":"1340","1360":"1360","ABT    1337":"circa 1337","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1302":"1302","about 1327":"circa 1327","1279":"1279","1388":"1388","1343":"1343","Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of,Is Coed,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llys Y Coed, Flintshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Wales":"Wales","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales","Glendower, Denbigh, Wales, United Kingdom":"Denbighshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Ascoli Piceno, Marche (Regione), Italy":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italië"},"en":{"1305–1337":"1305–1337","1302–1343":"1302–1343","1330–1388":"1330–1388","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1337–Male":"1337–Deceased","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1279–1340":"1279–1340","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1296":"1296","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","ABT    1337":"about 1337","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1302":"1302","about 1327":"about 1327","1279":"1279","1388":"1388","1343":"1343","Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Conway, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of,Is Coed,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llys Y Coed, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales","Glendower, Denbigh, Wales, United Kingdom":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Ascoli Piceno, Marche (Regione), Italy":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Goch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Pawel, Zuzanna, Zygmunt.","North German: habitational name from any of various minor places which get their names from an ancient Germanic element <i>goch</i>, <i>gog</i> ‘marsh, bog, fen’.","Polish: from a pet form of various personal names beginning with <i>Go-</i>, such as <i>Gościsław</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Gotch","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>coch</i>, <i>goch</i> ‘red(-haired)’; see   Gooch   3.","English (Northamptonshire): variant of   Gooch   1 and 2.","Americanized form of German <b>Götsch</b> (see   Gotsch  )."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor Goch was born in 1305, in Carmarthenshire, Wales, her father, Philip ab Ifor Lord of Iscoed, was 31 and her mother, Catherine ferch Llywelyn Ap Griffith, was 26. She married Thomas ap Llywelyn about 1327, in Cardiganshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1337, in Cardiganshire, Wales, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1305–1337":"1305–133